title: U.S. more closely monitoring cyberspace after Russian bombings in Syria, general says
text:
12 U.S. more closely monitoring cyberspace after Russian bombings in Syria, general says 
Army Times: The U.S. is monitoring the cyber landscape for potential threats that could emerge due to the conflict in Syria, Air Force Lt. Gen. James McLaughlin said Oct. 9, but he declined to comment on what sorts of cyber threats Russian involvement in the war could create.
